{
  "text": "One procedure commonly employed for sampling subepithelial lesions is the use of large-capacity (jumbo) forceps biopsies to perform a bite-on-bite technique. With a large-channel endoscope, the forceps are passed multiple times with each bite directly on top of the previous bite in an attempt to burrow into the lesion. Compared to that of conventional-sized forceps, the use of jumbo forceps may increase the surface area of the tissue sample but does not significantly increase its depth [CITATION_1] . Also, bleeding as a complication of this technique may be troublesome.",
  "citation_candidates": [
